  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Starting at 6th level, you pick up the pace, and showcase to your Summon how to signature scout technique.</p><p> Your Signature Summon gains access to their own set if Superiority Die, which are d4s.</p><p> The amount of Superiority Die they possess is equal to half your maximum amount of Superiority Die.</p><p> Your summon regains their spent Superiority Die on long rest, and can use the same manuevers that you can.</p><p> Your summon can only use one manuever per turn, and cannot perform a manuever you already used during the same turn.</p><p> Also, at 6th level, once per round when you or your summon would roll a natural 20 on attack roll, skill check, or saving throw, you can choose to regain one Superiority Die or have your Signature Summon regain 2 Superiority Die.</p><p></p>",
